Create com.loanflow.loanservice.controller.LoanApplicationController in loan-service:

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/v1/applications")
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class LoanApplicationController {

    private final LoanApplicationService loanApplicationService;

    // POST /api/v1/applications — APPLICANT only — 201 Created
    @PostMapping
    @PreAuthorize("hasRole('APPLICANT')")
    public ResponseEntity<CreateLoanApplicationResponse> createApplication(
            @RequestBody @Valid CreateLoanApplicationRequest request,
            @AuthenticationPrincipal Jwt jwt) {
        Long applicantUserId = jwt.getClaim("userId");
        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED)
                .body(loanApplicationService.createApplication(request, applicantUserId));
    }

    // GET /api/v1/applications/{applicationId} — APPLICANT, LOAN_OFFICER, ADMIN — 200 OK
    @GetMapping("/{applicationId}")
    @PreAuthorize("hasAnyRole('APPLICANT', 'LOAN_OFFICER', 'ADMIN')")
    public ResponseEntity<ApplicationDetailResponse> getApplicationById(
            @PathVariable Long applicationId,
            @AuthenticationPrincipal Jwt jwt) {
        Long userId = jwt.getClaim("userId");
        String role = jwt.getClaim("role");
        return ResponseEntity.ok(loanApplicationService.getApplicationById(applicationId, userId, role));
    }

    // GET /api/v1/applications — LOAN_OFFICER, ADMIN only — 200 OK paginated
    @GetMapping
    @PreAuthorize("hasAnyRole('LOAN_OFFICER', 'ADMIN')")
    public ResponseEntity<ApplicationSearchResponse> searchApplications(
            @RequestParam(required = false) LoanStatus status,
            @RequestParam(required = false) LoanType loanType,
            @RequestParam(defaultValue = "0") int page,
            @RequestParam(defaultValue = "20") int size,
            @RequestParam(defaultValue = "submittedAt,desc") String sort) {
        return ResponseEntity.ok(
                loanApplicationService.searchApplications(status, loanType, page, size, sort));
    }

    // PATCH /api/v1/applications/{applicationId}/status — LOAN_OFFICER, ADMIN only — 200 OK
    @PatchMapping("/{applicationId}/status")
    @PreAuthorize("hasAnyRole('LOAN_OFFICER', 'ADMIN')")
    public ResponseEntity<UpdateApplicationStatusResponse> updateStatus(
            @PathVariable Long applicationId,
            @RequestBody @Valid UpdateApplicationStatusRequest request,
            @AuthenticationPrincipal Jwt jwt) {
        Long actingUserId = jwt.getClaim("userId");
        return ResponseEntity.ok(
                loanApplicationService.updateStatus(applicationId, request, actingUserId));
    }
}

Create com.loanflow.loanservice.config.SecurityConfig in loan-service:

@Configuration
@EnableMethodSecurity
public class SecurityConfig {

    @Bean
    public SecurityFilterChain filterChain(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {
        return http
            .csrf(csrf -> csrf.disable())
            .sessionManagement(sm -> sm.sessionCreationPolicy(SessionCreationPolicy.STATELESS))
            .authorizeHttpRequests(auth -> auth
                .requestMatchers("/actuator/health").permitAll()
                .anyRequest().authenticated())
            .oauth2ResourceServer(oauth2 -> oauth2.jwt(Customizer.withDefaults()))
            .build();
    }
}

Ensure the following dependencies are present in backend/loan-service/pom.xml (version managed by loanflow-parent):
- spring-boot-starter-security
- spring-boot-starter-oauth2-resource-server

